âœ… Infrastructure Automation using Terraform + Ansible

ðŸ› ï¸ Practical Work:

Step 1: Create New EC2 (Ubuntu 22.04)
- AWS Console se EC2 launch karo
- Region: us-east-2
- Instance Type: t2.micro
- OS: Ubuntu 22.04
- Security Group: Allow port 22 (SSH) + 80 (HTTP)
- Ye step EC2 create karne ke liye hai jahan Terraform kaam karega

Step 2: SSH Into EC2 & Install Required Tools
ssh kar ke connect ho jao aur commands run karo:
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y unzip curl gnupg software-properties-common
- Ye tools Terraform aur Ansible ke liye required hain

Step 3: Install AWS CLI
curl "https://awscli.amazonaws.com/awscli-exe-linux-x86_64.zip" -o "awscliv2.zip"
unzip awscliv2.zip
sudo ./aws/install
aws --version
- Ye step AWS CLI install kar ke EC2 ko AWS ke sath authenticate karta hai

Step 4: Install Terraform
curl -fsSL https://apt.releases.hashicorp.com/gpg | gpg --dearmor | sudo tee /usr/share/keyrings/hashicorp-archive-keyring.gpg > /dev/null
echo "deb [signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/hashicorp-archive-keyring.gpg] https://apt.releases.hashicorp.com $(lsb_release -cs) main" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/hashicorp.list
sudo apt update
sudo apt install terraform -y
terraform -version
- Ye step Terraform install karta hai jo infrastructure create karega

Step 5: Install Ansible
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y ansible
ansible --version
- Ansible install hota hai taake software install aur configure ho sake

Step 6: Configure AWS CLI
aws configure
# Access Key ID: [paste here]
# Secret Access Key: [paste here]
# Region: us-east-2
# Output format: json
- Ye step IAM user credentials se AWS CLI configure karta hai

Step 7: Setup SSH Key for Ansible
ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -f ~/.ssh/id_rsa -N ""
cat ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub
- Public key copy kar ke EC2 me add karni hai, Ansible ke liye

Step 8: Project Directory Structure & Terraform Code
mkdir terraform-ansible
cd terraform-ansible
- main.tf create karo aur paste karo Terraform code jo:
  - AWS provider setup
  - Key pair create
  - Security group allow SSH & HTTP
  - EC2 instance with local-exec Ansible provisioner
- Ye step Terraform se infrastructure create karne ke liye hai

Step 9: Write Ansible Playbook
- playbook.yml create karo
- Paste karo:
  - Install Apache
  - Upload custom index.html
- Ye step software install aur webpage configure karta hai

Step 10: Initialize and Apply Terraform
terraform init
terraform plan
terraform apply
- Type "yes" to confirm
- Ye step poori infrastructure automate karta hai: EC2 create + Apache install + webpage serve

âœ… Final Output:
- EC2 created with Terraform
- Apache installed automatically via Ansible
- Custom HTML served on new EC2's public IP
- Browser me IP open karke test karo: http://<public-ip>

